      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "f_p2t_80",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 34,
      "y": 914,
      "width": 892,
      "height": 114,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "g_f_p2"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 259,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 260,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "PHASE 2 \u2014 Multi-host\n\nTrigger: a single Docker host's CPU/memory capacity becomes the actual bottleneck.\n\nHand-rolled scheduler (a handful of hosts, simple placement rule) \u2192 Kubernetes only once\nhand-rolled scheduling / health-checks / rolling-restarts become the real pain. Namespace-per-\ncompany gives the same isolation Phase 1's docker networks give, fleet-wide.",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "PHASE 2 \u2014 Multi-host\n\nTrigger: a single Docker host's CPU/memory capacity becomes the actual bottleneck.\n\nHand-rolled scheduler (a handful of hosts, simple placement rule) \u2192 Kubernetes only once\nhand-rolled scheduling / health-checks / rolling-restarts become the real pain. Namespace-per-\ncompany gives the same isolation Phase 1's docker networks give, fleet-wide.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 10
    },
    {
